    "summary": "Teyo van der Schoot holds a Master Degree in Rural Sociology & Development Studies (1986) from the Wageningen Agricultural University in the Netherlands. Through SNV (Dutch organisation for technical assistance and development cooperation) he has worked 8 years in Peru, in Quechua communities in Puno, and with farmers\u2019 movement Rondas Campesinas in Cajamarca. Since 1997 he has workeds with Hivos (humanist institute for development cooperation). For several years he managed the portfolio of some 30 counterparts in Bolivia and Ecuador. Thematic areas included Microfinance, Organic Agriculture, Community Forestry, Gender, Human Rights, Arts & Culture. In 2005 he became Programme Manager for Human Rights & Democratisation at Hivos, leading a team of 10 staff members at head office and regional offices of Hivos, with a yearly portfolio of 12 million euro of partnerships in the global south. Between 2011 and 2016 he was Senior Advisor on Human Rights at Hivos in The Hague. From that position he presided the Dutch Human Rights Coalition (BBO) for two years. He also ran the secretariate of the 2014 and 2015 Human Rights Tulip Award for the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs. Particular focus was on a NWO funded Hivos and ISS collaboration developing action research and capacity building for environmental justice with indigenous peoples in the Amazon region. As an independent consultant since spring 2016, he was part of the team that obtained a \u20ac 15 million project with the Dutch Postcode Lottery enabling a coalition of Hivos, Greenpeace, COICA, ISS a.o., to equip indigenous communties with satellite, drones, and mobile information technology for defending their territories against environmental crimes. In 2019 he joined Impunity Watch in The Hague, Netherlands, as Latin America Program Advisor.",
